tldr: The user requested a comprehensive review of the sleep questionnaire
  application against its acceptance criteria and the implementation of
  identified missing features. The agent successfully implemented a tiredness
  severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome detection,
  weighted EDS scoring, expanded CSV export, and added pain/chronic fatigue
  screening.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the Statement of Work and
  detailed specification. The primary goal was to identify and implement missing
  acceptance criteria. The agent systematically addressed several critical gaps.
  This included integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with
  safety warnings for high scores, and implementing detection logic for complex
  conditions like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Weighted scoring for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness was added for more accurate assessment.
  Furthermore, the agent expanded the CSV export to capture all questionnaire
  data, ensuring comprehensive data access. New questions were introduced to
  screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue, enhancing the diagnostic
  capabilities of the questionnaire. All changes were consistently applied
  across the application, including the interactive report and the PDF
  generation, providing a more robust and informative user experience.
